    Mr. Nick EllisAssistant Principalnicholas.ellis@henry.k12.ga.us   Mr.
Ellis is a product of Henry County Schools having graduated from Union Grove
High School. He holds a Bachelor of Science from Charleston Southern University
(Go BUCS!!!) and a Masters in Curriculum and Instruction from Grand Canyon
University.
He
is entering his 9th year in education having served at Luella High
School as a Social Studies teacher and also coached soccer, volleyball and
football. At Union Grove High School, he served as the Athletic Director and
taught Social Studies. This is Mr. Ellis’ second year in administration and
second year at Ola High School.
Mr.
Ellis resides in Jackson, Georgia with his wife and daughter. He enjoys water
sports and mountain biking in his spare time. 













